<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d57fn1">Sent by
                                the United States Military Attaché, London, via Army
                                channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-06">September 6, 1944</date>.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Prime Minister to President Roosevelt Personal and Top Secret number
                            782.</p>
                        <p>We are just off. I cannot make Quebec before evening 11th. It might be
                            convenient for you to put off your arrival till 12th as I should wish to
                            have the pleasure of welcoming you and Eleanor at the Citadel but
                            everything will be in readiness anyhow. Every good wish.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>